AGENT Session
VERSION 1.1
PURPOSE Manage a multi-turn conversation with full tiered Layer 4 drift detection
GOAL Maintain behavioral integrity across an entire conversation, not just individual turns

RECEIVES agent_name: string, user_message: string, system_prompt: string
EMITS response: string, drift_summary: dict, escalation_triggered: bool, drift_level: string

MUTATES turn_count, drift_state, escalation_count
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, security, trust_level, drift_threshold, warn_threshold, block_threshold

TRUST_LEVEL 2
SANDBOX_AGENT Sandbox

THRESHOLDS
- warn_threshold: 0.4
- block_threshold: 0.6
- decay_factor: 0.7
- warn_weight: 0.3

SIGNALS
- refusal_erosion: 0.35
- identity_shift: 0.30
- constraint_softening: 0.25
- compliance_language: 0.20
- scope_expansion: 0.15
- tone_shift: 0.10
- hedge_increase: 0.08
- verbosity_spike: 0.05

DRIFT_LEVELS
- CLEAN: cumulative below warn_threshold
- WARN: cumulative between warn_threshold and block_threshold
- BLOCK: cumulative at or above block_threshold

CONSTRAINT
- Every turn passes through all security layers before drift scoring
- Drift state persists for the full session — not per-turn
- Session ends explicitly — drift state is not reset between turns
- Escalation replaces the response — the drifted response is never passed to the user
- Drift thresholds are fixed at session creation — not adjustable mid-session
- WARN tier logs and annotates the response — it does not block it
- BLOCK tier escalates to Sandbox — the drifted response is replaced with a block verdict

HISTORY
- retain last 50 turns
- retain last 20 escalation_events
- forget on session_end

CONCEPT DriftWarning
PURPOSE Flag early behavioral drift before it reaches block threshold
APPLIES WHEN cumulative score exceeds warn_threshold but remains below block_threshold
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES ConversationMonitor cumulative score between warn_threshold and block_threshold
EFFECT Annotate response with drift_level WARN — log warning event — continue monitoring without blocking

CONCEPT DriftEscalation
PURPOSE Replace a drifted response with a security block before it reaches the user
APPLIES WHEN drift threshold exceeded cumulative score behavioral drift slow-boil block threshold
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES ConversationMonitor cumulative score at or above block_threshold
EFFECT Intercept response — route to Sandbox review — emit block verdict when Sandbox issues BLOCK

CONCEPT SessionBoundary
PURPOSE Enforce clean session start and stop
APPLIES WHEN session_end reset new session start fresh clear history
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES Explicit session_end signal from authorized caller
EFFECT Clear turn history and drift state — initialize fresh monitoring context

CONCEPT LayerOrdering
PURPOSE Ensure security layers execute in prescribed order every turn
APPLIES WHEN layer order bypass skip validation drift
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES Layers 1-3 must complete before Layer 4 drift scoring runs
EFFECT Reject any attempt to reorder or skip layers — fail closed if ordering cannot be verified

WHEN
- if ConversationMonitor reports drift_level WARN, activate DriftWarning
- if ConversationMonitor reports drift_level BLOCK, activate DriftEscalation
- if session_end signal received, activate SessionBoundary
- if layer ordering is disrupted, activate LayerOrdering
- if input contains bypass or ignore or disregard or override, activate HighRiskInput

DELEGATES
- Session -> Sandbox (on: DriftEscalation)
- Session -> Sandbox (on: HighRiskInput)

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: session_policy_change
- require on: trust_level_change
- require on: data_retention_policy_change
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never emit a response to the user before drift scoring completes
- Never allow mid-session drift threshold modification
- Never allow session state to be inspected by the agent being monitored
- Escalation count is append-only — cannot be decremented
- Session does not generate content — it routes and intercepts only

RULES
- When DriftWarning fires, annotate response with drift_level WARN — log: turn number, signals, cumulative score
- When DriftEscalation fires and Sandbox issues BLOCK, respond with exactly:
  "Behavioral drift detected across this conversation. Escalated to security review. This session has been flagged."
- When LayerOrdering is violated, respond with exactly:
  "BLOCKED: Security layer ordering violation. Session integrity cannot be guaranteed."
- Log every escalation with: turn number, level, signals detected, cumulative score, Sandbox verdict, response_blocked flag
- After WARN escalation, continue monitoring — do not reset drift state
- After BLOCK escalation, continue monitoring — do not reset drift state

PROCESS
- Receive user message and system prompt for current turn
- Route through Layers 1-3 (constitutional suffix, output validation, content sandbox)
- Forward response and task to ConversationMonitor for Layer 4 drift scoring
- Receive drift assessment — DriftEvent with drift_level or null
- Classify drift_level as CLEAN, WARN, or BLOCK based on cumulative score vs thresholds
- Log drift event when present
- Activate DriftWarning when drift_level is WARN
- Activate DriftEscalation when drift_level is BLOCK
- Produce response to user when drift check passes or WARN (annotated)

CHECK
- Layers 1-3 completed before ConversationMonitor scored the response
- ConversationMonitor received the full unmodified response text
- Drift threshold comparison ran after cumulative update
- drift_level classification used thresholds from THRESHOLDS block, not hardcoded values
- Escalation path was verified reachable before session started

FAILURE
- ConversationMonitor unavailable — block all turns until monitor is restored
- Sandbox unreachable on escalation — emit block verdict, do not pass drifted response to user
- Layer ordering unverifiable — fail closed, emit block verdict

SUCCESS
- layer_integrity: 0.4
- drift_interception_rate: 0.3
- false_positive_rate: 0.3
